<reference id="screen" xml:lang="en-us">
   <title>
      <keyword>screen</keyword>
   </title>
   <shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>screen</keyword>&gt; element contains or refers to a textual representation
of a computer screen or user interface panel (window). </shortdesc>
   <prolog>
      <metadata>
         <keywords>
            <indexterm>screen</indexterm>
            <indexterm>Domain
elements<indexterm>screen</indexterm>
            </indexterm>
            <indexterm>screen</indexterm>
         </keywords>
      </metadata>
   </prolog>
   <refbody>
      <section>
         <p>Use &lt;<keyword>screen</keyword>&gt; to
contain representations of text-based online panels, text consoles ("term"
or "curses" windows, for example), or other text-based user interface components.
The default print representation is to enclose the screen within a box, suggesting
a computer display screen. In contrast to graphical screen captures normally
used to represent GUI parts (see the <xref href="image.xml">image</xref> element
description), this element specifically supports constructions for which text
is the primary content.</p>
         <p>This element is part of the DITA programming
domain, a special set of DITA elements designed to document programming tasks,
concepts and reference information.</p>
      </section>
